Name: Huye
Description: Huye is the third city of Rwanda, located in the south. It was formerly known as Butare and many maps and official documents still refer to Butare.  Huye is the capital of Huye district, which was again Butare district prior to its dissolution in 2006.  It is said to have about 80,000 inhabitants. It is famous for hosting the National University, the National Museum (unique in Africa) and being near to Nyanza, where the palace of the former king (the so-called mwami) is.

Name: Kibuye
Description: Kibuye is a city in Rwanda.  Located on the shore of Lake Kivu, the surrounding area offers some stunning views of the lake. The new Name is Karongi, most people still refer to Kibuye though.
